news.title: JPMorgan seeks to attract staff with $3 billion skyscraper in New York
news.para: JPMorgan Chase has unveiled its new 60-story headquarters in Manhattan.  It is designed to attract and retain talent, serving as a model for future global offices. The bank has also upgraded workstations in several international locations and plans further enhancements.

news.title: Nimbus projects adds ₹1,100 crore development potential with favourable order from UP government
news.para: UPIDA has directed the Yamuna authority to recalculate land allotment for Nimbus Projects, granting an additional 1.1 million sq ft with a Rs 1,100 crore development potential. This order, following a revision petition, resolves a long-pending issue for the IITL-Nimbus project. The company also reported a rise in sales bookings and collections for Q2 FY 2025-26.

news.title: Ahmedabad’s urban body tells developers to maintain percolation wells for BU permit
news.para: Ahmedabad Urban Development Authority (Auda) now mandates developers to maintain percolation wells for building use permission, requiring notarized affidavits for operational status. This move reinforces existing regulations, as Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation also collects deposits for well maintenance, aiming to combat waterlogging and ensure groundwater recharge.

news.title: Telangana to unlock more land auction after ₹3,135-crore Raidurg record
news.para: Following a record-breaking land sale, Telangana is auctioning another prime parcel in Hyderabad's Knowledge City for an estimated Rs 200 crore. This move signals the state's strategy to monetize high-value urban land amid strong investor demand in the city's western corridor, known for its IT and financial ecosystem.

news.title: Marathon Nextgen Realty & Adani Realty to jointly develop commercial project in Mumbai
news.para: Marathon Nextgen Realty has partnered with Adani Realty to develop Monte South Commercial, a 1.2 million sq ft office and retail project in Byculla, Mumbai. This development, with an estimated gross value of ₹3,400 crore, is part of the larger Monte South campus, which also includes four residential towers.

news.title: Institutional-grade malls now form 30–35% of India’s 650 operational malls: Report
news.para: India's retail malls are becoming more professional. Many now meet high standards, attracting significant investment. Developers are building larger, experience-focused malls. This trend is expanding beyond major cities into smaller hubs. New GST reforms are expected to boost transparency and investor confidence, further fueling growth in the organized retail sector.

news.title: Private equity inflows in Indian real estate fall 15% in H1 FY26: Report
news.para: Private equity real estate investments in India moderated in H1 FY26, with inflows down 15% year-on-year to USD 2.2 billion. While deal concentration eased, retail, mixed-use, and office sectors saw increased traction, and foreign capital rebounded, contributing 73% of inflows.

news.title: Indian retail REITs may touch ₹80,000 crore by 2030: Report
news.para: Retail REITs are projected to become a significant ₹60,000–80,000 crore opportunity by 2030, potentially forming 30-40% of India's total REIT market. This growth is driven by maturing Grade A malls, rising urban incomes, and steady consumption, with tier-II cities emerging as key growth hotspots for new retail developments.

news.title: Redevelopment projects to unlock over 44,000 new homes in Mumbai: Report
news.para: Mumbai's society redevelopment projects are set to deliver 44,277 new homes by 2030, valued at ₹1,305 billion. Over 910 housing societies have signed development agreements since 2020, unlocking significant land potential. Western Suburbs lead this transformation, with Borivali, Andheri, and Bandra emerging as key redevelopment hotspots.

news.title: India’s retail sector records 2.4 million sq ft of leasing volume in Q3 2025: Report
news.para: India's retail sector demonstrated robust growth in Q3 2025, with gross leasing volume reaching 2.41 million sq ft across top cities, a 7.6% quarter-on-quarter increase. Year-to-date volumes surged 25.2% year-on-year, indicating strong occupier demand and positioning the sector to surpass 2024's full-year GLV. Malls and high streets both saw increased absorption, with domestic retailers dominating leasing activity.

news.title: India office absorption hits 59.6 million sq ft in 9M 2025: Report
news.para: India's office market achieved a historic high in absorption during the first nine months of 2025, reaching 59.6 million sq ft. Bengaluru led leasing activity, with technology companies, GCCs, and BFSI firms driving demand. The market anticipates continued growth, fueled by premium asset demand and robust GCC expansion.

news.title: India records 57 million sq ft absorption across top six cities: Report
news.para: India's office market demonstrated robust growth in 2025, with 56.8 million sq ft absorbed in the first nine months, driven by Global Capability Centres and IT-BPM sectors. Despite a slight Q3 dip, total leasing is projected to exceed 75 million sq ft by year-end, with healthy occupier activity and easing vacancy rates.

news.title: Over 87,000 residential units sold in Q3 2025: Report
news.para: Indian housing sales remain strong in Q3 2025, defying expectations of a price correction. Mumbai leads sales, while Chennai sees significant growth. Premium housing is now the dominant segment, with sales above one crore rupees increasing. New launches see a slight dip, but the market signals continued demand and a healthy inventory level.

news.title: India's office space stock crosses 1 billion sq ft in Q3 2025: Report
news.para: India's office market saw a 24% year-on-year surge in gross leasing to 66.7 million sq ft in the first nine months of 2025. Bengaluru led leasing activity, while Global Capability Centres and IT services drove demand. Rents rose across major markets, and vacancy levels declined as India's office stock surpassed 1 billion sq ft.

news.title: Karnataka HC overturns order on approving firm’s modified building plan
news.para: A division bench of the Karnataka High Court has overturned a single-judge order that compelled the BBMP to approve a modified building plan for Sangam Enterprises. The court ruled that the modified plan, which sought significant setback relaxation using a TDR certificate, did not comply with rules notified after the application was submitted.

news.title: Bombay HC orders builder to pay daily penalty for failing to secure fire NOC
news.para: Bombay High Court mandates a daily Rs 50,000 penalty for builders failing to secure Fire NOC for Kandivali West flats by December 31, 2025.  This stern ruling follows a decade-long delay, impacting flat owners' ability to occupy their homes due to missing essential safety certificates and occupation permits.

news.title: Two Pune civic body's officials suspended for overlooking illegal construction
news.para: In a decisive move to uphold building regulations, the Pune Municipal Corporation has put a halt to the employment of two officials from their TDR department. These individuals have been implicated in failing to prevent the unauthorized construction of additional floors on a property, with work already progressing to the seventh floor.

news.title: Austria: Rene Benko appeals against insolvency fraud conviction
news.para: Austrian property tycoon Rene Benko is appealing his two-year jail sentence for insolvency fraud. A court convicted him for moving money to his mother before his company Signa collapsed. Prosecutors are also appealing his acquittal on a separate charge. The Signa bankruptcy is Austria's largest since World War Two. Investigations into further alleged crimes continue.

news.title: Charity commissioner orders 'status quo' in sale of  Jain trust's property to Pune builder
news.para: In a significant move, Pune's Charity Commissioner Amogh Kaloti has intervened to stop the impending sale of a valuable property that accommodates a Jain boarding facility and temple. The property, spanning 12,000 square meters, was poised to be sold to a private developer for Rs 311 crore.

news.title: Holcim to buy walling specialist Xella for 1.85 billion euros
news.para: Holcim is set to make more major acquisitions in the coming months. The company recently bought German firm Xella for 1.85 billion euros. This move aims to tap into Europe's growing refurbishment market. Holcim is focusing more on sustainable building products. The acquisition is expected to boost earnings in the first year.
